Class ConstrainedRVEA

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.strategy.MOStrategy

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC

    public class ConstrainedRVEA
extends RVEA
    The RVEA strategy for problems with constraints.

    Paper: R. Cheng, Y. Jin, M. Olhofer, B. Sendhoff. “A Reference Vector Guided Evolutionary Algorithm for Many-Objective Optimization”, IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation, vol. 20, no. 5, pp. 773-791. 2016.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • createSolutionComparator

        public void createSolutionComparator(java.util.Comparator<net.sf.jclec.IFitness>[] components)
        Create the solution comparator.

        RVEA uses a Pareto comparator.

        In case it is needed, this version of RVEA uses a Pareto comparator for constrained problems.

        Overrides:
        createSolutionComparator in class RVEA
        Parameters:
        components - The set of simple comparators for each objective.
